catalog_courses.title: Software Project Management
catalog_courses.description: This course will teach software engineering students how to plan, track and communicate the status of large-scale software projects to a diverse group of stakeholders. Using modern traditional and Agile software development methodologies and tools, and emulating a realistic software development project, students will be immersed in the activities used by industry to develop, manage, and monitor the development of a software product throughout the semester. Students will learn planning, tracking, risks, cost monitoring, and agile team collaboration.
